# Architecture principles

Follow **SOLID**, **DRY**, **YAGNI**, **KISS**. Code must be easy to review file-by-file.

## Layer map (never mix)

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| UI | `src/components/**`, `src/app/**/page.tsx` | Render, events, local UI state only |
| Hooks | `src/hooks/**` | Wire UI to data; no Prisma, no raw SQL |
| Server services | `src/server/**` | Business rules, orchestration, auth checks |
| Domain engine | `src/session-engine/**` | Pure functions: dice, room reducers, validators |
| Data access | `src/server/**` or `src/lib/db.ts` | Prisma queries only; no JSX |
| API | `src/app/api/**` | HTTP boundary: parse input, call service, return DTO |
| Infra | `src/lib/**` | db, storage, auth config |

**Forbidden in React components:** Prisma calls, `db.`, business rules, dice math, role/permission checks.

**Forbidden in `session-engine/`:** React imports, hooks, fetch, Prisma.

## SOLID (practical)

- **S** - One file, one reason to change. Split when UI + logic grow together.
- **O** - Extend via new scene types / services, not `if` chains in components.
- **L** - Shared interfaces in `src/types/`; mocks match production shapes.
- **I** - Small props and service methods; no god objects.
- **D** - UI depends on hooks/services, not Prisma or S3 clients directly.

## DRY

- Extract duplication on the **third** repeat, not the first.
- Shared logic -> `session-engine/` or `server/`, never copy-paste across components.
- Shared UI -> `components/shared/`; shared types -> `src/types/`.

## YAGNI

- No abstractions for one use case (generic "GameEngineFactory" with one game).
- No extra env flags, feature toggles, or plugins until requested.
- Ship the minimal path; delete dead code in the same PR.

## KISS

- Prefer flat folders and readable names over clever patterns.
- Prefer server service + hook over Redux/global store unless justified.

## File size guide

- Components: aim **< 150 lines**; split layout vs content.
- Services: one domain per file (`games.ts`, `sessions.ts`).
- Pages: thin - fetch via server service, pass data to components.

## Review-friendly PRs

- One concern per PR (e.g. "session join API" not "refactor + new feature").
- New feature = types -> engine/service -> API -> hook -> UI (in that order when possible).
